Yeah, it's inspired

14:54.913 --> 14:56.948
by business class
airport lounges.

14:56.948 --> 15:00.319
It's a big step up from eating
by myself in the bathroom.

15:00.319 --> 15:01.987
I saved you a seat,

15:01.987 --> 15:06.358
and feel free to put your books
on my buttshelf.

15:06.358 --> 15:08.460
Aw! Thanks, JFK.

15:08.460 --> 15:10.629
Looks like
we're both popular now.

15:10.629 --> 15:13.732
- You two are so cute together.
- Right?

15:13.732 --> 15:18.571
- Joan? Joan? Joan of Arc?
- It's cool. He's with me.

15:18.571 --> 15:20.139
♪ (ROCK MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪

15:20.139 --> 15:21.907
Oh, my God, Abe,

15:21.907 --> 15:24.176
how is the Unity Luncheon
planning?

15:24.176 --> 15:27.079
Well, I decided
we're gonna have tables.

15:27.079 --> 15:29.147
Uh-huh. And we're gonna put
food on the tables,

15:29.147 --> 15:32.153
and then we'll eat the food
off those same tables.

15:33.652 --> 15:35.220
Tables, that's, uh,
that's--

15:35.220 --> 15:37.155
Anything else? 'Cause I'm--
I'm sure you've got more.

15:37.155 --> 15:39.825
I'm sure of that, 'cause I--
I can vouch for that, you know,

15:39.825 --> 15:43.194
- as I did earlier, publicly.
- Oh, and chairs.

15:43.194 --> 15:45.597
I don't want
everybody to sit Indian style.

15:46.898 --> 15:48.833
Oops, sorry, I-- I didn't mean
to say something gay.

15:51.106 --> 15:51.970
Abe!

15:51.970 --> 15:53.838
Okay. Let me explain.

15:53.838 --> 15:55.306
When I said gay, I'm not--

15:55.306 --> 15:57.608
I'm trying to say
that it was the most dumb,

15:57.608 --> 15:59.978
stupid, horrible thing
that you could ever imagine.

15:59.978 --> 16:01.947
- Abe!
- Like, just the worst thing

16:01.947 --> 16:04.152
in the world.

16:06.287 --> 16:08.920
Hey, you! So, um,
I like it in here

16:08.920 --> 16:10.656
and I don't wanna
get kicked out.

16:10.656 --> 16:11.990
So, it would be great

16:11.990 --> 16:13.858
if you went off
and thought about

16:13.858 --> 16:15.526
those lunch plans
a little more, you know?

16:15.526 --> 16:20.533
Before you step in it
any further. Somewhere far away.

16:20.533 --> 16:22.601
Oh. Okay.

16:22.601 --> 16:26.440
♪ (EMOTIONAL MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

16:31.779 --> 16:34.813
My old thinking dock.

16:34.813 --> 16:37.177
Why is this so dangerously high?

16:37.177 --> 16:38.384
Climate change, bro.

16:38.384 --> 16:40.052
So, that was real? Hmm.

16:40.052 --> 16:41.448
What are you doing out here

16:41.448 --> 16:43.454
at the thinking docks,
Confucius?

16:43.454 --> 16:45.657
Oh, I'm just trying
to get better at thinking,

16:45.657 --> 16:47.959
be more like the Confucius
I'm cloned from.

16:47.959 --> 16:51.262
Seems to me, there's no telling
what to think these days.

16:51.262 --> 16:53.331
You know, normally,
I'd check in with my bro Gandhi

16:53.331 --> 16:56.401
at times like this.
I think he's been avoiding me.

16:58.537 --> 17:00.972
Why does everything
have to change?

17:00.972 --> 17:02.802
Joan and I used to be so close,

17:02.802 --> 17:05.243
but now I can't even sit
at the same lunch table as her.

17:05.243 --> 17:07.612
Everything I say is wrong.

17:07.612 --> 17:09.314
I just can't get it right.

17:09.314 --> 17:11.511
- What should I do?
- What I've learned

17:11.511 --> 17:13.586
is the very best thing
to do always

17:13.586 --> 17:16.221
is to just say you're sorry.

17:16.221 --> 17:17.789
Hmm. That's--

17:17.789 --> 17:20.826
- ♪ (EMOTIONAL MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪
- In a cool,
overproduced apology video.

17:20.826 --> 17:23.461
Sounds foolproof. Let's do it.

17:23.461 --> 17:25.798
- ♪ (U.S. ANTHEM PLAYING) ♪
- I wanna offer an apology

17:25.798 --> 17:27.431
for my despicable behavior.

17:27.431 --> 17:31.169
This is an opportunity to learn,
and reflect, and grow.

17:31.169 --> 17:34.372
As well as learning
and reflecting while growing.

17:34.372 --> 17:38.146
I'm not the only one
that matters. All lives matter.

17:39.180 --> 17:41.079
Uh. I'm sorry
if I offended anyone,

17:41.079 --> 17:43.314
but the truth is,
I don't see color.

17:43.314 --> 17:46.251
I mean, I once dressed up
as Chris Tucker for Halloween.

17:46.251 --> 17:50.088
Sorry not sorry.
I refuse to apologize.

17:50.088 --> 17:52.560
I'm sorry, I said,
"Sorry not sorry."

17:53.427 --> 17:55.594
I said I was sorry.

17:55.594 --> 17:57.661
So, I made
a couple mistakes, huh?

17:57.661 --> 18:02.267
Or is it "mister-stakes" now?
Oh, let's not be ridiculous.

18:02.267 --> 18:05.370
Or-- Or do I have to say
"ri-vagina-ulous," huh?

18:05.370 --> 18:08.473
Because you can't comprehend
like a bunch of girls.

18:08.473 --> 18:10.809
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

18:10.809 --> 18:14.412
<i>I'm sorry.
I'm sorry. I'm sorry. Ah!</i>

18:14.412 --> 18:16.848
- ♪ (MELANCHOLY MUSIC PLAYING) ♪
- This guy is tragic.

18:16.848 --> 18:18.650
Are you sure he isn't a Kennedy?

18:18.650 --> 18:21.389
- Oh, Abe!
- I'll make it up to you.

18:22.389 --> 18:25.459
Not gonna happen.
Abraham Lincoln,

18:26.026 --> 18:28.693
you are canceled.

18:36.234 --> 18:39.771
Joan, what's happening?
Is this washable paint?

18:39.771 --> 18:41.674
Joan, say something.

18:44.712 --> 18:46.578
Joan?

18:48.212 --> 18:49.280
♪ (MELANCHOLY MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪

18:49.280 --> 18:53.484
- Hey, Abe. You okay?
- No, I'm not.

18:53.484 --> 18:55.854
And you just stood there
and let them cancel me.

18:55.854 --> 18:57.022
Oh-- Oh, hey,

18:57.022 --> 18:59.257
I tried to include you
every step of the way.

18:59.257 --> 19:00.993
There's only so much
I can do, Abe.

19:00.993 --> 19:02.994
Who even are you right now?

19:02.994 --> 19:05.564
Eating lunch with JFK
and all the popular people,

19:05.564 --> 19:06.898
we used to make fun of them.

19:06.898 --> 19:08.900
This is different.
They actually like me.

19:08.900 --> 19:10.368
And I wanted them
to like you too.

19:10.368 --> 19:12.170
But you made it impossible,
didn't you?

19:12.170 --> 19:14.540
Now, I have to pull this whole
Unity Luncheon together

19:14.540 --> 19:15.841
in one day by myself.

19:15.841 --> 19:16.875
Well, good luck...

19:16.875 --> 19:17.909
...'cause I'm gonna plan

19:17.909 --> 19:19.610
my own unity luncheon...

19:19.610 --> 19:23.348
...and I'm gonna call it,
"The Luncheon for Unity,"

19:23.348 --> 19:26.217
and I'm gonna get
100,000 chicken hot wings,

19:26.217 --> 19:30.088
so that people will come
to my party, not yours.

19:31.957 --> 19:35.261
Almost there.
Keep doing the finger guns.

19:37.932 --> 19:39.464
The next time Candide
places a match

19:39.464 --> 19:41.599
against the wick
of this lavender vanilla insult,

19:41.599 --> 19:44.036
she'll find only too late
that I have replaced it

19:44.036 --> 19:48.106
with this humble stick
of "dianamité."

19:48.106 --> 19:50.742
Mr. B, did you embed dynamite
in this candle?

19:50.742 --> 19:53.979
I'm not allowed
in here, remember?

19:53.979 --> 19:56.080
And put razor blades
in the shell soap?

19:56.080 --> 19:59.150
- Nope!
- And a harpoon in the toilet

19:59.150 --> 20:01.420
that is activated
by the flushing mechanism?

20:04.292 --> 20:05.423
Why, the only other person

20:05.423 --> 20:07.425
with access
to the executive washroom...

20:07.425 --> 20:11.429
...is--
Candide was trying to kill me.

20:11.429 --> 20:16.637
Candide was trying to...
...kill-- kill me.

20:21.142 --> 20:23.308
Wait a minute.
I've never worn pearls.

20:23.308 --> 20:26.044
Candide must have
gotten these for me.

20:26.044 --> 20:31.385
Oh! They're bombs!

20:32.519 --> 20:35.086
Wow, Joan, this is impressive.

20:35.086 --> 20:37.455
You pulled together
a hella swizz Unity Luncheon.

20:37.455 --> 20:40.259
Thanks, guys. Hey,
you haven't seen Abe, have you?

20:40.259 --> 20:41.493
He said something about doing

20:41.493 --> 20:43.261
his own unity lunch...

20:43.261 --> 20:44.897
...but I'm sure he wouldn’t--

20:44.897 --> 20:47.298
♪ (UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

20:49.267 --> 20:52.471
I've got 100,000
hot wings right here.

20:52.471 --> 20:55.106
America's most beloved
party food,

20:55.106 --> 20:59.243
only served
at my Luncheon for Unity.

20:59.243 --> 21:00.846
So unfair.
I was just trying

21:00.846 --> 21:02.814
to impress a woman
I ignored for years,

21:02.814 --> 21:06.484
and then I get canceled.
Oh, women are so hard to please.

21:06.484 --> 21:09.688
- Seriously, man.
- Thank you, Ivan the Terrible.

21:09.688 --> 21:11.956
Finally someone gets how I feel.

21:11.956 --> 21:13.358
I hate all women.

21:13.358 --> 21:15.193
I hate them because
I want to have sex with them

21:15.193 --> 21:17.295
and they won't have sex with me
because I hate them.

21:17.295 --> 21:20.132
Okay.
That's not quite how I feel.

21:20.132 --> 21:21.995
Wait, there's more than one
unity luncheon?

21:21.995 --> 21:25.173
I want my own unity luncheon!

21:39.417 --> 21:42.255
- ♪ (UPBEAT MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪
- Unity Week is ruined.

21:42.255 --> 21:43.988
- Joan--
- It's okay, Frida.

21:43.988 --> 21:45.489
You don't have to say it.

21:45.489 --> 21:48.760
I'm no longer included
in the Inclusivity Committee.

21:48.760 --> 21:49.994
I'm so sorry, girl.

21:49.994 --> 21:52.100
- ♪ (EMOTIONAL MUSIC PLAYING) ♪
- Me too.

21:55.298 --> 21:56.370
No!

21:58.005 --> 22:02.607
Oh, we were so close.

22:02.607 --> 22:06.075
I guess high school
is gonna be the same after all.

22:11.385 --> 22:13.822
I think I screwed up,
drugstore tiki torch.

22:31.072 --> 22:33.207
Ow! Dinger! Paper cut.

22:36.811 --> 22:38.446
Ow! Dinger! Paper cut.

22:40.815 --> 22:41.883
Ow! Dinger!

22:46.453 --> 22:50.221
Ow! Dinger!
Ding-- Dinger! Ow! Dinger!

22:50.221 --> 22:52.224
♪ (EMOTIONAL MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪

22:52.224 --> 22:54.321
Dinger!

22:54.321 --> 22:57.395
Oh! Ah!

22:57.395 --> 22:59.330
♪ (ROCK MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

22:59.330 --> 23:02.435
Attention everyone.

23:02.435 --> 23:04.670
Today I ruined much more
than a luncheon.

23:04.670 --> 23:07.171
I ruined the best friendship
I've ever had

23:07.171 --> 23:09.440
with the best person
I've ever known.

23:09.440 --> 23:12.745
Joan is creative, and funny,
and deserves to be popular.

23:12.745 --> 23:16.481
I deserve to be punished.
And for that punishment,

23:16.481 --> 23:20.719
I deserve to have hot wing sauce
poured into these paper cuts.

23:20.719 --> 23:22.420
Who's with me?

23:22.420 --> 23:26.695
Sorry, who's against me?

23:36.303 --> 23:39.137
♪ (ROCK MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪

23:39.137 --> 23:40.305
Hey, Joan, uh...

23:40.305 --> 23:41.339
...there's a really boring

23:41.339 --> 23:42.875
black-and-white
film festival tomorrow.

23:42.875 --> 23:43.775
You wanna come with us?

23:43.775 --> 23:46.414
Of course. Thanks, guys.

23:47.315 --> 23:48.780
Uh. I'm sorry, Joan.

23:48.780 --> 23:50.649
I don't know much
about this crazy new world

23:50.649 --> 23:51.617
we're living in.

23:51.617 --> 23:54.252
But I do know that you make it
a better place.

23:54.252 --> 23:56.489
I really hope
we can be friends again.

23:56.489 --> 23:59.557
Oh, Abe, I always wanna
be your friend.

23:59.557 --> 24:03.161
Whether it's 2003
or 2000 and whatever this is.

24:03.161 --> 24:04.363
Do you think we could ever maybe

24:04.363 --> 24:06.932
- be more than frie--
- Hey, JFK!

24:06.932 --> 24:08.100
♪ (UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

24:08.100 --> 24:10.836
So, I've been thinking
about your proposal,

24:10.836 --> 24:14.106
and the more I think about it,
the more I realize,

24:14.106 --> 24:15.408
I'm thinking too much.

24:15.408 --> 24:16.842
What I'm trying to say is,

24:16.842 --> 24:18.443
I'd love to be your girlfriend.

24:18.443 --> 24:22.784
I say we celebrate
with some tongue twisting, huh?

24:24.084 --> 24:25.150
Red leather,
yellow leather!

24:25.150 --> 24:26.184
Red leather, yellow leather!

24:26.184 --> 24:28.520
She sells seashells
by the seashore!

24:28.520 --> 24:29.621
All right.

24:29.621 --> 24:32.190
Now, let's kiss
in the French style,

24:32.190 --> 24:35.894
